00:11:26.510 --> 00:11:27.870
You get to pay for lunch today.

00:11:27.870 --> 00:11:30.370
Like, the waitresses are always
like, that's so mean of you.

00:11:30.370 --> 00:11:31.560
And I'm like, no,
you don't get it.

00:11:31.560 --> 00:11:33.190
Like, they're getting points
and I'm paying them anyway.

00:11:33.190 --> 00:11:34.023
CLIFF REDEKER: Yeah.

00:11:34.023 --> 00:11:35.129
5x.

00:11:35.129 --> 00:11:36.920
BRIAN KELLY: So loyalty
can save you money.

00:11:36.920 --> 00:11:39.294
So sticking with a hotel chain
that might be a little bit

00:11:39.294 --> 00:11:40.930
extra, but if
you're going to get

00:11:40.930 --> 00:11:45.424
the free Wi-Fi and the perks
and be comfortable and rested,

00:11:45.424 --> 00:11:47.590
you know, it may make sense
to pay a little bit more

00:11:47.590 --> 00:11:50.300
for a flight to build status,
to get the free checked bag.

00:11:50.300 --> 00:11:53.650
So I would just encourage
cost center managers

00:11:53.650 --> 00:11:54.910
to see the bigger picture.

00:11:54.910 --> 00:11:57.451
Because I think the big problem
in America is a lot of times,

00:11:57.451 --> 00:12:00.850
we go with the very cheapest
flight, and cheap is expensive.

00:12:00.850 --> 00:12:03.880
So try to think a
little bit higher level.

00:12:03.880 --> 00:12:06.030
But you know, loyalty,
especially at the top tiers,

00:12:06.030 --> 00:12:07.140
can really pay off.

00:12:07.140 --> 00:12:08.244
And let's be honest.

00:12:08.244 --> 00:12:09.410
Business travel is grueling.

00:12:09.410 --> 00:12:10.720
It's time away from home.

00:12:10.720 --> 00:12:11.440
It's exhausting.

00:12:11.440 --> 00:12:14.569
It's bad for your health.

00:12:14.569 --> 00:12:17.110
So being able to be comfortable
and stick with a hotel chain,

00:12:17.110 --> 00:12:18.370
even if it costs
a little bit more,

00:12:18.370 --> 00:12:20.440
I think benefits the
business in the long run.

00:12:20.440 --> 00:12:20.670
CLIFF REDEKER: Yeah.

00:12:20.670 --> 00:12:21.760
And then you hit
the ground running.

00:12:21.760 --> 00:12:22.468
You're not tired.

00:12:22.468 --> 00:12:24.580
You can go straight to
the meeting, or whatever.

00:12:24.580 --> 00:12:26.000
And there are other businesses.

00:12:26.000 --> 00:12:28.910
Google has a very generous
policy in terms of money

00:12:28.910 --> 00:12:31.350
