So we run all of our social
spend on credit cards,

00:18:07.460 --> 00:18:08.850
and the first
100,000 we get, I'm

00:18:08.850 --> 00:18:10.210
getting 300,000 Amex points.

00:18:10.210 --> 00:18:12.849
So to pay $175 or
$195 for that card,

00:18:12.849 --> 00:18:14.890
I'm getting 200,000 extra
points than if I put it

00:18:14.890 --> 00:18:15.556
on another card.

00:18:15.556 --> 00:18:18.300
So I really focus-- and
you can win at this game

00:18:18.300 --> 00:18:20.100
by just staying
above board and just

00:18:20.100 --> 00:18:21.810
playing by the rules they set.

00:18:21.810 --> 00:18:22.860
It's pretty lucrative.

00:18:22.860 --> 00:18:23.000
CLIFF REDEKER: Yeah.

00:18:23.000 --> 00:18:24.330
Keeping it legal is
something that's--

00:18:24.330 --> 00:18:25.200
BRIAN KELLY: Keeping it legal.

00:18:25.200 --> 00:18:25.700
Exactly.

00:18:25.700 --> 00:18:27.780
[LAUGHTER]

00:18:27.780 --> 00:18:29.350
Using credit cards
for jail bonds.

00:18:29.350 --> 00:18:30.683
That's a good blog post.

00:18:30.683 --> 00:18:31.516
CLIFF REDEKER: Yeah.

00:18:31.516 --> 00:18:34.600
And then redeeming the points
for champagne in the Delta Sky

00:18:34.600 --> 00:18:35.200
Clubs

00:18:35.200 --> 00:18:35.700
BRIAN KELLY: Yeah.

00:18:35.700 --> 00:18:36.616
Little sparkling wine.

00:18:36.616 --> 00:18:38.050
I don't think they
have champagne.

00:18:38.050 --> 00:18:39.049
CLIFF REDEKER: Prosecco.

00:18:39.049 --> 00:18:40.992
BRIAN KELLY: Not to mince words.

00:18:40.992 --> 00:18:43.450
CLIFF REDEKER: And then we had
another question from Janine

00:18:43.450 --> 00:18:44.060
as well.

00:18:44.060 --> 00:18:47.116
She was wondering, are you
an American million miler?

00:18:47.116 --> 00:18:48.490
Are such things
worth it anymore?

00:18:48.490 --> 00:18:50.448
BRIAN KELLY: I'm not a
million miler, actually.

00:18:50.448 --> 00:18:52.130
So I think I'm, like, 700,000.

00:18:52.130 --> 00:18:55.595
So I actually wasn't-- so
American used to be able to get

00:18:55.595 --> 00:18:57.970
million miler status by you
spending on your credit card.

00:18:57.970 --> 00:18:59.386
It was the one
airline that would.

00:18:59.386 --> 00:19:03.850
So back in the day, I
wasn't big into churning,

00:19:03.850 --> 00:19:06.701
so I didn't get the
two million just

00:19:06.701 --> 00:19:07.950
by spending on my credit card.

00:19:07.950 --> 00:19:09.920
So I'm doing it the
old-fashioned way, which I'll

00:19:09.920 --> 00:19:11.086
get there in a couple years.

00:19:11.086 --> 00:19:14.340
But I mean, the million
mile status sounds amazing,

00:19:14.340 --> 00:19:16.290
but it's really the
lowest level elite status.

00:19:16.290 --> 00:19:17.790
Which these days, the
airlines have watered down

00:19:17.790 --> 00:19:20.280
so much that you basically get
the same from a Coburn credit

00:19:20.280 --> 00:19:20.780
card.

00:19:20.780 --> 00:19:24.420
So as much as it's a
nice pat on the back--

00:19:24.420 --> 00:19:26.116
and that's another
lesson I urge people,

00:19:26.116 --> 00:19:28.240
is I call it the elite
status hamster wheel, right?

00:19:28.240 --> 00:19:29.270
Like so many people--
elite status.

00:19:29.270 --> 00:19:29.860
I'm cool.

00:19:29.860 --> 00:19:30.760
I'm part of the club.

00:19:30.760 --> 00:19:32.500
Well, you know, the
lower level elite

00:19:32.500 --> 00:19:34.800
statuses these days
have been watered down

00:19:34.800 --> 00:19:35.930
and benefits ripped apart.

00:19:35.930 --> 00:19:38.090
You can't even select
a premium economy seat

00:19:38.090 --> 00:19:39.954
on United and Delta now.

00:19:39.954 --> 00:19:41.120
They're really pulling back.

00:19:41.120 --> 00:19:44.370
So you know, yes, it's nice to
have some airline elite status.

00:19:44.370 --> 00:19:46.480
But especially in a
town like San Francisco,

00:19:46.480 --> 00:19:50.270
United silver status
is worth as much as--

00:19:50.270 --> 00:19:52.020
CLIFF REDEKER: Yeah,
this bottle of water.

00:19:52.020 --> 00:19:52.520
Yeah.

00:19:52.520 --> 00:19:54.980
Well, and even,
there's so many 1Ks

00:19:54.980 --> 00:19:57.010
flying, like, SFO to O'Hare.

00:19:57.010 --> 00:20:00.450
I mean, executive platinum
status doesn't always clear.

00:20:00.450 --> 00:20:03.869
And to that end as
well, I'm proud to say,

00:20:03.869 --> 00:20:06.160
I made executive platinum
for the first time this year.

00:20:06.160 --> 00:20:06.300
BRIAN KELLY: Woohoo!

00:20:06.300 --> 00:20:06.770
[APPLAUSE]

00:20:06.770 --> 00:20:07.870
CLIFF REDEKER: A little
mini accomplishment.

00:20:07.870 --> 00:20:08.750
BRIAN KELLY: Halfway
through the year, too.

00:20:08.750 --> 00:20:09.490
That's pretty impressive.

00:20:09.490 --> 00:20:09.810
CLIFF REDEKER: Yeah.

00:20:09.810 --> 00:20:11.810
Well, it's a lot of
that business class.

00:20:11.810 --> 00:20:14.840
And went to Penang,
Malaysia for the fun

00:20:14.840 --> 00:20:18.820
back through Cathay
First to Vancouver.

00:20:18.820 --> 00:20:19.960
It's great this year.

00:20:19.960 --> 00:20:21.827
Next year, it's still
kind of questionable.

00:20:21.827 --> 00:20:22.660
Still up in the air.

00:20:22.660 --> 00:20:24.493
We're not sure about
the spend requirements.

00:20:24.493 --> 00:20:27.540
BRIAN KELLY: Well, I
think the last two years,

00:20:27.540 --> 00:20:30.906
we've seen a lot of change with
the US Airways merger settling.

00:20:30.906 --> 00:20:32.530
All the major mergers
have settled now.

00:20:32.530 --> 00:20:35.024
You know, we're still
waiting on Alaska and Virgin.

00:20:35.024 --> 00:20:36.440
But in general, I
think we've gone

00:20:36.440 --> 00:20:38.023
through a really big
period of change.

00:20:38.023 --> 00:20:39.632
And I think I
hopefully-- maybe I'm

00:20:39.632 --> 00:20:40.840
just too much of an optimist.

00:20:40.840 --> 00:20:42.214
I see over the
next couple years,

00:20:42.214 --> 00:20:45.899
there's not to be too much
drastic change going on.

00:20:45.899 --> 00:20:48.440
We're still waiting to see with
the Marriott-Starwood merger.

00:20:48.440 --> 00:20:50.210
There's huge question
marks there with how

00:20:50.210 --> 00:20:51.370
that's going to go down.

00:20:51.370 --> 00:20:53.670
And that could affect
future hotel mergers.

00:20:53.670 --> 00:20:56.390
But I think in
general, I mean, I'm

00:20:56.390 --> 00:20:58.880
looking forward
to some stability.

00:20:58.880 --> 00:21:01.810
I don't think there's going
to be major devaluations.

00:21:01.810 --> 00:21:04.480
Unless you're Delta, which
devalues on a weekly basis.

00:21:04.480 --> 00:21:05.340
CLIFF REDEKER: It's
all a mystery there.

00:21:05.340 --> 00:21:06.673
BRIAN KELLY: It's all a mystery.

00:21:06.673 --> 00:21:07.680
There's no award charts.

00:21:07.680 --> 00:21:09.221
CLIFF REDEKER: And
so for those of us

00:21:09.221 --> 00:21:11.270
that just joined, what
are the best fringe

00:21:11.270 --> 00:21:13.340
benefits to take advantage
of besides the cafe

00:21:13.340 --> 00:21:16.150
lounges, the cabanas, the
salt-and-pepper squid?

00:21:16.150 --> 00:21:19.090
Anything that people might
not normally think of?

00:21:19.090 --> 00:21:22.653
BRIAN KELLY: I mean, one
of the new lounges, Amex

00:21:22.653 --> 00:21:24.934
has Centurion lounges,
which they just

00:21:24.934 --> 00:21:26.100
opened in Houston this week.

00:21:26.100 --> 00:21:27.280
San Francisco's really nice.

00:21:27.280 --> 00:21:28.696
So these are
actually lounges that

00:21:28.696 --> 00:21:30.440
are-- I think a lot
of airline lounges

00:21:30.440 --> 00:21:32.340
have dropped in quality.

00:21:32.340 --> 00:21:35.050
So the Amex platinum's $450.

00:21:35.050 --> 00:21:38.840
Off the bat, you get a
$200 airline fee credit.

00:21:38.840 --> 00:21:40.897
And it says you can only
use it for airline fees,

00:21:40.897 --> 00:21:43.230
but in reality, you can
actually get airline gift cards.

00:21:43.230 --> 00:21:45.679
So every year, I get
four $50 AA gift cards.

00:21:45.679 --> 00:21:47.720
So my $450 a year platinum
card all of the sudden

00:21:47.720 --> 00:21:50.680
costs me $250 for Delta lounge
access and unlimited lounge

00:21:50.680 --> 00:21:53.175
access to these Centurion
lounges, which at SFO is

00:21:53.175 --> 00:21:55.140
wine tasting, two free guests.

00:21:55.140 --> 00:21:55.890
Everything's free.

00:21:55.890 --> 00:22:00.190
There's no up charges like
cheap other American carriers

00:22:00.190 --> 00:22:02.710
that charge for premium cheese.

00:22:02.710 --> 00:22:07.280
So I think-- and
points are great,

00:22:07.280 --> 00:22:08.890
but perks can be even better.

00:22:08.890 --> 00:22:10.960
So there are credit
cards out there.

00:22:10.960 --> 00:22:11.820
The Citi Prestige.

00:22:11.820 --> 00:22:13.110
Yes, there's terrible
news this week.

00:22:13.110 --> 00:22:14.360
They're changing next year you.

00:22:14.360 --> 00:22:15.610
Can't get into the AA lounges.

00:22:15.610 --> 00:22:18.170
But the best benefits
still-- it's mildly tweaked,

00:22:18.170 --> 00:22:21.530
but you get the fourth night
free of any hotel, basically,

00:22:21.530 --> 00:22:22.950
including corporate rates.

00:22:22.950 --> 00:22:26.140
See, that benefit
alone is unbelievable.

00:22:26.140 --> 00:22:28.634
You can get many
thousands a year

00:22:28.634 --> 00:22:29.800
for paying for that benefit.

00:22:29.800 --> 00:22:33.040
Plus you also get a
$250 airline credit.

00:22:33.040 --> 00:22:36.260
So cheap is expensive is
another thing with credit cards,

00:22:36.260 --> 00:22:39.021
that annual fee cards
frankly suck, you know?

00:22:39.021 --> 00:22:40.520
Like, that's not
where the value is.

00:22:40.520 --> 00:22:42.520
So sometimes paying
an annual fee--

00:22:42.520 --> 00:22:44.780
but dig into the benefits.

00:22:44.780 --> 00:22:46.950
CLIFF REDEKER: And
percent, you know, like 1%

00:22:46.950 --> 00:22:48.840
back may not always
be the best option

00:22:48.840 --> 00:22:51.740
if you get that in cash versus
the value you have for travel.

00:22:51.740 --> 00:22:52.000
BRIAN KELLY: Yeah.

00:22:52.000 --> 00:22:52.970
A lot of people call
me and say, well, I

00:22:52.970 --> 00:22:54.320
have a Capital One card.

00:22:54.320 --> 00:22:56.009
I'm getting 1% or 2% back.

00:22:56.009 --> 00:22:57.050
And those cards are fine.

00:22:57.050 --> 00:22:58.289
And those cards are great.

00:22:58.289 --> 00:22:59.080
But think about it.

00:22:59.080 --> 00:23:02.330
You spend $100,000, and it'll
give you $2,000 in travel.

00:23:02.330 --> 00:23:04.940
You spend $100,000 on a couple
other cards, you get bonuses,

00:23:04.940 --> 00:23:06.939
you're going to Asia three
times in first class.

00:23:06.939 --> 00:23:09.860
So you can buy two
economy tickets

00:23:09.860 --> 00:23:13.490
to Europe, or if you get
bonuses on other cards

00:23:13.490 --> 00:23:19.330
and transfer and get-- so the
fixed value cards are slow,

00:23:19.330 --> 00:23:19.830
steady.

00:23:19.830 --> 00:23:21.160
There's no devaluations.

00:23:21.160 --> 00:23:23.760
But there's also
little upside as well.

00:23:23.760 --> 00:23:25.990
You're never going to get
more than a cent in value

00:23:25.990 --> 00:23:27.510
for a Capital One point, ever.

00:23:27.510 --> 00:23:28.470
No matter who you are.

00:23:28.470 --> 00:23:28.969
I can't.

00:23:28.969 --> 00:23:32.260
You know, like, so
with that stability

00:23:32.260 --> 00:23:35.020
comes the lack of upside.

00:23:35.020 --> 00:23:36.770
CLIFF REDEKER: Well,
and transitioning now

00:23:36.770 --> 00:23:39.880
to thepointsguy.com,
the sort of media empire

00:23:39.880 --> 00:23:42.390
that you're building here,
the first question I had

00:23:42.390 --> 00:23:44.570
is, how do you balance
information sharing

00:23:44.570 --> 00:23:45.570
with deal crashing?

00:23:45.570 --> 00:23:47.414
Is the tragedy of the
commons inevitable?

00:23:47.414 --> 00:23:48.080
BRIAN KELLY: No.

00:23:48.080 --> 00:23:53.980
I mean, we used to get a lot
of flak for posting deals.

00:23:53.980 --> 00:23:55.700
In this day and age
of social media,

00:23:55.700 --> 00:23:58.020
deals spread like wildfire.

00:23:58.020 --> 00:24:00.030
My take is if it's going
to benefit our readers,

00:24:00.030 --> 00:24:00.670
then that's it.

00:24:00.670 --> 00:24:01.670
We're going to share it.

00:24:01.670 --> 00:24:03.920
Now if it's gray
area bending rules,

00:24:03.920 --> 00:24:06.240
we're probably not going
to because our policy is,

00:24:06.240 --> 00:24:08.073
let's just stay above
board with everything.

00:24:08.073 --> 00:24:10.830
And we have ethics that
we'd like to stick to.

00:24:10.830 --> 00:24:11.369
But, yeah.

00:24:11.369 --> 00:24:12.660
In terms of deals, we share it.

00:24:12.660 --> 00:24:13.770
That's the whole
point of the website.

00:24:13.770 --> 00:24:15.603
That's why we've doubled
in size every year.

00:24:15.603 --> 00:24:17.880
And that's why people
come to us and trust us.

00:24:17.880 --> 00:24:20.560
We don't take freebies
from any airlines.

00:24:20.560 --> 00:24:23.960
All of our reviews are
paid for by ourselves.

00:24:23.960 --> 00:24:25.760
So I stick to that.

00:24:25.760 --> 00:24:29.910
And people who come
into it and then-- this

00:24:29.910 --> 00:24:31.700
is an amazing, amazing hobby.

00:24:31.700 --> 00:24:32.910
Whatever you want to call it.

00:24:32.910 --> 00:24:33.550
It's amazing.

00:24:33.550 --> 00:24:35.758
Once you're part of the
club, like many other things,

00:24:35.758 --> 00:24:37.240
people want to shut
the doors down.

00:24:37.240 --> 00:24:40.020
But that's not the
society we live in.

00:24:40.020 --> 00:24:42.655
And there will
never be doors shut.

00:24:42.655 --> 00:24:44.280
I mean, yes, there's
some secret groups

00:24:44.280 --> 00:24:46.238
out there for frequent
flyers that share deals,

00:24:46.238 --> 00:24:47.470
and that's great.

00:24:47.470 --> 00:24:50.580
But in general, we're going
to share the information.

00:24:50.580 --> 00:24:53.359
And I mean, I thrive off of now.

00:24:53.359 --> 00:24:55.150
I mean, I see people
every day in airports.

00:24:55.150 --> 00:24:57.470
I'm six foot, 7",
so I'm easy to spot.

00:24:57.470 --> 00:24:58.980
And people share stories.

00:24:58.980 --> 00:25:00.350
All of our email's positive.

00:25:00.350 --> 00:25:02.000
People whose lives
have been changed.

00:25:02.000 --> 00:25:02.860
CLIFF REDEKER: Reader
success stories.

00:25:02.860 --> 00:25:03.650
BRIAN KELLY: Reader
success stories

00:25:03.650 --> 00:25:05.240
of people who got
married and, you know,

00:25:05.240 --> 00:25:07.300
their rocky, long-distance
relationship all of the sudden

00:25:07.300 --> 00:25:08.540
became a lot more
doable, because they were

00:25:08.540 --> 00:25:09.706
able to see each other more.

00:25:09.706 --> 00:25:12.850
So that's what I focus on.

00:25:12.850 --> 00:25:14.184
Not the naysayers or the trolls.

00:25:14.184 --> 00:25:15.558
CLIFF REDEKER:
No, no the haters.

00:25:15.558 --> 00:25:16.440
Yeah, no haters.

00:25:16.440 --> 00:25:18.130
And then if you want to
share a little bit more

00:25:18.130 --> 00:25:19.880
about the sort of
business side of things,

00:25:19.880 --> 00:25:24.290
like is there a dollar figure of
money that circulates through?

00:25:24.290 --> 00:25:27.400
Like, is the referral bonus
sustainable for bloggers?

00:25:27.400 --> 00:25:28.150
BRIAN KELLY: Yeah.

00:25:28.150 --> 00:25:30.667
I mean, the business that
we've created is really unique.

00:25:30.667 --> 00:25:32.000
It's affiliate marketing, right?

00:25:32.000 --> 00:25:33.580
So almost all of
our revenue comes

00:25:33.580 --> 00:25:36.530
from people who get credit
cards on our websites.

00:25:36.530 --> 00:25:39.880
Or motto is, we have a
staff of about 10 now,

00:25:39.880 --> 00:25:44.060
and 20 contributors that we
pay I think pretty fairly.

00:25:44.060 --> 00:25:45.540
But you know, the site's free.

00:25:45.540 --> 00:25:47.620
So even the app is free.

00:25:47.620 --> 00:25:51.080
And it costs a lot of money
to run this business, office

00:25:51.080 --> 00:25:51.789
in New York.

00:25:51.789 --> 00:25:53.080
So the affiliate model's great.

00:25:53.080 --> 00:25:56.740
I mean, our readers, you're
going to get the best offer.

00:25:56.740 --> 00:25:59.890
So it's like, if you can give
a credit card company $100

00:25:59.890 --> 00:26:01.720
or give The Points
Guy, that we'll

00:26:01.720 --> 00:26:03.600
invest in more
content that's suited

00:26:03.600 --> 00:26:05.950
to you, that's a no-brainer.

00:26:05.950 --> 00:26:07.560
And credit card
companies in the past,

00:26:07.560 --> 00:26:10.620
the best we've been
given-- had issues with,

00:26:10.620 --> 00:26:12.630
is the best offer
really being available?

00:26:12.630 --> 00:26:16.660
I stand by-- we offer the
best publicly available deal.

00:26:16.660 --> 00:26:18.880
Yeah, sometimes you
can go incognito

00:26:18.880 --> 00:26:20.790
in the checkout
process, and maybe

00:26:20.790 --> 00:26:24.030
get a special offer that you
can kind of tweak the system.

00:26:24.030 --> 00:26:25.405
But we can't, in
a blog post when

00:26:25.405 --> 00:26:27.080
we're writing about a deal, we
write about the best publicly

00:26:27.080 --> 00:26:27.900
available offer.

00:26:27.900 --> 00:26:30.922
So sometimes you can tweak
the system to get better,

00:26:30.922 --> 00:26:32.380
and people will
say-- but I'm like,

00:26:32.380 --> 00:26:33.360
we have three million readers.

00:26:33.360 --> 00:26:33.820
I can't.

00:26:33.820 --> 00:26:35.778
In every blog post, we're
talking about United,

00:26:35.778 --> 00:26:38.390
say, well maybe if some
people go through this channel

00:26:38.390 --> 00:26:40.510
and tweak it this
way-- so in general,

00:26:40.510 --> 00:26:42.090
we offer the best deals.

00:26:42.090 --> 00:26:46.010
And the business is amazing.

00:26:46.010 --> 00:26:46.740
I'm proud of it.

00:26:46.740 --> 00:26:49.450
And we're heavily
investing in video now.

00:26:49.450 --> 00:26:52.100
We just relaunched our
TPG TV series, which

00:26:52.100 --> 00:26:53.440
follows me around the world.

00:26:53.440 --> 00:26:56.480
And it's not just, oh, look
at me drinking champagne

00:26:56.480 --> 00:26:59.100
on a plane, which is fun.

00:26:59.100 --> 00:27:02.940
But it's like tangible--
we cut the size down,

00:27:02.940 --> 00:27:06.807
and it's tangible tricks
that you can also share.

00:27:06.807 --> 00:27:08.890
Like "How to Book Singapore
Suites in 90 Seconds,"

