GooglersGive team helps

00:37:47.480 --> 00:37:50.200
us donate our time, money,
and effort to various causes.

00:37:50.200 --> 00:37:53.110
And so we have a badge to
donate station for the Points

00:37:53.110 --> 00:37:55.260
for Peace in the PeaceJam.

00:37:55.260 --> 00:37:57.810
And so I wanted to just talk
to you a little bit about that.

00:37:57.810 --> 00:37:59.070
How did you get started on that?

00:37:59.070 --> 00:38:00.695
What's been the sort of
rewarding experiences

00:38:00.695 --> 00:38:01.540
you've seen from it?

00:38:01.540 --> 00:38:02.540
BRIAN KELLY: Oh my gosh.

00:38:02.540 --> 00:38:04.620
PeaceJam-- so the
business was successful.

00:38:04.620 --> 00:38:06.510
And finding a charity
is kind of hard.

00:38:06.510 --> 00:38:09.005
Like, everyone's like,
what's your ultimate passion

00:38:09.005 --> 00:38:09.530
in charity?

00:38:09.530 --> 00:38:11.940
And you're like, I mean,
I'm a giving person,

00:38:11.940 --> 00:38:13.979
and it's hard to pick
a charity that aligns

00:38:13.979 --> 00:38:15.020
with what you love doing.

00:38:15.020 --> 00:38:17.470
And I think charity work is
just much like your work life,

00:38:17.470 --> 00:38:17.970
right?

00:38:17.970 --> 00:38:20.469
So once you really align and
figure out what you love doing,

00:38:20.469 --> 00:38:23.220
you'll succeed much quicker than
randomly being placed in a job.

00:38:23.220 --> 00:38:25.312
So you know, charity
for me for a while

00:38:25.312 --> 00:38:27.020
was just writing checks
to organizations,

00:38:27.020 --> 00:38:29.100
but I realized that
wasn't very fulfilling.

00:38:29.100 --> 00:38:30.940
A friend came to me
one day and was like,

00:38:30.940 --> 00:38:31.860
I have to talk to you.

00:38:31.860 --> 00:38:33.530
In college, I was
involved with PeaceJam.

00:38:33.530 --> 00:38:34.946
I think you'll
absolutely love it.

00:38:34.946 --> 00:38:38.880
So PeaceJam is an
organization that Meng,

00:38:38.880 --> 00:38:40.887
the former Jolly Good
Fellow of Google,

00:38:40.887 --> 00:38:42.720
who I've been working
with-- so he now works

00:38:42.720 --> 00:38:45.320
with PeaceJam full time on this
Billion Acts of Peace campaign.

00:38:45.320 --> 00:38:47.611
The whole point is taking
the work of Nobel Peace Prize

00:38:47.611 --> 00:38:49.780
winners, 13 of the most
inspiring in the world--

00:38:49.780 --> 00:38:53.359
Dalai Lama, Desmond
Tutu, Rigoberta Menchu--

00:38:53.359 --> 00:38:55.150
taking their teachings,
making a curriculum

00:38:55.150 --> 00:38:56.200
to kids around the world.

00:38:56.200 --> 00:38:57.980
So Points for Peace
was launched this year

00:38:57.980 --> 00:39:00.563
with the hopes of having people
be able to donate their points

00:39:00.563 --> 00:39:01.630
and miles, their money.

00:39:01.630 --> 00:39:03.671
You can actually earn
points by using your credit

00:39:03.671 --> 00:39:05.187
card to donate for them.

00:39:05.187 --> 00:39:07.520
And I think we can all agree
the world needs more peace,

00:39:07.520 --> 00:39:08.670
more so than ever.

00:39:08.670 --> 00:39:10.720
And as much as we
want to put our head

00:39:10.720 --> 00:39:14.660
in the sand with crazy
news stories every day,

00:39:14.660 --> 00:39:16.070
it's not all terrible.

00:39:16.070 --> 00:39:17.181
It's so inspiring.

00:39:17.181 --> 00:39:18.930
There's youth around
the world that really

00:39:18.930 --> 00:39:20.630
want to make a difference.

00:39:20.630 --> 00:39:24.300
So in Ghana-- yeah.

00:39:24.300 --> 00:39:25.790
So through Points
for Peace, we're

00:39:25.790 --> 00:39:29.540
helping in Guatemala,
Ghana, South Africa, India,

00:39:29.540 --> 00:39:30.850
and East Timor.

00:39:30.850 --> 00:39:33.006
There's these budding
movements of kids there

00:39:33.006 --> 00:39:34.630
who learn all year
long the curriculum,

00:39:34.630 --> 00:39:36.838
and then we bring and use
points to bring the Nobels,

00:39:36.838 --> 00:39:39.365
and they do two-day
jams, the PeaceJam.

00:39:39.365 --> 00:39:40.490
So I was working with Meng.

00:39:40.490 --> 00:39:42.490
We're bringing it to Singapore.

00:39:42.490 --> 00:39:43.366
And it's amazing.

00:39:43.366 --> 00:39:45.490
I'm mean, to be able to
see these Nobel Peace Prize

00:39:45.490 --> 00:39:48.037
winners who have been
through-- you think

00:39:48.037 --> 00:39:49.120
you've been through a lot.

00:39:49.120 --> 00:39:51.495
You hear-- you know, Rigoberta
Menchu, whose whole family

00:39:51.495 --> 00:39:54.410
was assassinated during the
36-year civil war in Guatemala.

00:39:54.410 --> 00:39:56.550
And for me, even being
able to be around them,

00:39:56.550 --> 00:39:57.690
I get so much out of it.

00:39:57.690 --> 00:39:59.640
So we're bringing
these Nobels to kids

00:39:59.640 --> 00:40:01.420
to help them better
their communities,

00:40:01.420 --> 00:40:03.720
and hopefully create
a whole new generation

00:40:03.720 --> 00:40:05.367
of nonviolent leaders.

00:40:05.367 --> 00:40:06.950
So Points for Peace,
we just launched.

00:40:06.950 --> 00:40:09.390
And we're working with
all the credit card

00:40:09.390 --> 00:40:10.470
companies and airlines.

00:40:10.470 --> 00:40:12.303
You know, they all have
their own charities,

00:40:12.303 --> 00:40:15.910
and it's political, but
we're making great progress.

00:40:15.910 --> 00:40:17.970
You Singapore Airlines
just did a match.

00:40:17.970 --> 00:40:21.580
If any of you have Singapore
Airlines miles, up to 250,000

00:40:21.580 --> 00:40:22.430
donated.

00:40:22.430 --> 00:40:23.890
You can even donate
1,000 of them.

00:40:23.890 --> 00:40:25.580
They'll match to us.

00:40:25.580 --> 00:40:27.610
And the airlines are
on board with it.

00:40:27.610 --> 00:40:33.562
So it's our first year, but
I foresee us growing it.

00:40:33.562 --> 00:40:35.020
And at a certain
point, I was like,

00:40:35.020 --> 00:40:37.400
we've just got to launch
and continue to evolve it.

00:40:37.400 --> 00:40:39.060
CLIFF REDEKER: And there's a
spot for readers too to, like,

00:40:39.060 --> 00:40:40.226
lend their travel expertise.

00:40:40.226 --> 00:40:41.905
Like, be a volunteer,
point maximizers.

00:40:41.905 --> 00:40:43.530
BRIAN KELLY: So the
goal is that people

00:40:43.530 --> 00:40:45.240
will be able to donate
points-- right now,

00:40:45.240 --> 00:40:46.156
you can donate points.

00:40:46.156 --> 00:40:48.490
