staffers to Guatemala,
because that's

00:40:52.032 --> 00:40:54.240
the best use of British
Airways on short-haul flights

00:40:54.240 --> 00:40:55.270
on American.

00:40:55.270 --> 00:40:57.750
So we have people who have
knowledge on how to use points,

00:40:57.750 --> 00:41:00.230
and then we have
people donating points.

00:41:00.230 --> 00:41:02.460
So our goal is to just
grow, and have these growing

00:41:02.460 --> 00:41:04.020
pools of points to help.

00:41:04.020 --> 00:41:07.850
Because frankly, charities
really get killed with travel.

00:41:07.850 --> 00:41:09.350
Travel is really
hard for charities,

00:41:09.350 --> 00:41:10.840
especially when you're going
to the developing world.

00:41:10.840 --> 00:41:13.190
Just to send one conference
staffer to East Timor

00:41:13.190 --> 00:41:14.660
is like $3,000.

00:41:14.660 --> 00:41:18.130
But it's only, like,
70,000 United miles.

00:41:18.130 --> 00:41:21.410
So we're helping
maximize miles for good

00:41:21.410 --> 00:41:23.400
is the general point
of Points for Peace.

00:41:23.400 --> 00:41:25.108
CLIFF REDEKER: And
you can check that out

00:41:25.108 --> 00:41:27.850
at the table in the back, or
also on The Points Guy website.

00:41:27.850 --> 00:41:28.530
BRIAN KELLY: And
none of the money

00:41:28.530 --> 00:41:30.590
actually goes to the Points--
it all goes to PeaceJam.

00:41:30.590 --> 00:41:32.060
The Points for Peace
is just the initiative.

00:41:32.060 --> 00:41:33.893
So we're not trying to
create a new charity.

00:41:33.893 --> 00:41:36.100
We're just trying to help
charities that already

00:41:36.100 --> 00:41:38.260
have something amazing
going on, and to take it

00:41:38.260 --> 00:41:39.050
to the next level.

00:41:39.050 --> 00:41:39.418
